records.addlTxt: 10:08 AM Defendant Jesse Pasek in court with  Attorney Matthew Krische. Mr. Pasek will be waiting his PH.  Attorney Jon D. Seifert in court for State of Wisconsin. Court advises of right to PH.  Court finds Mr. Pasek kvi waives his statutory right to PH.  State, based on Mr. Pasek's waiver will file an Information and will electronically file.  It will be the same as the complaint.  Both parties ask the court approve DAGPA to count 1.  Mr. Pasek has no criminal history at 38 years old.  He will plead guilty to count 2, a misdemeanor, pay the costs of case $443 and State would move to dismiss count 3.  State has spoke with law enforcement regarding resolution.  18 month agreement on the felony with conditions therein.   Believe this is an appropriate resolution.  Mr. Krische agrees to the agreement and has filed the PLQ and deferred agreement.  Court advised defendant of charges in count 1/max. penalties of complaint that mirrors the Information; advised of count 2/max. penalties and reviews his constitutional rights he will be giving up.  Mr. Krische believes factual basis for plea.  Court finds Mr. Pasek KVI waives his constitutional rights and there is a factual basis for his plea.  Defendant pleads no contest to count 1 and count 2.  Court will accept his plea to count 2 defer acceptance on count 1 and dismiss count 3.  Sentencing comments of Attorney Krische and ask Court accept the joint resolution.   You will need to identify the C/S project and have it approved by Gina of the Judge's Office by 10/21 and complete all hours within 5 months from that.  16 hours per month and complete by 3/21.  Total hours are 80.  Advised of appeal rights.  Order $443 in costs on count 2 to be paid within 10 days.
